name: 7 Seas Fish Market on Fourth
address: 7 Seas Fish Market on Fourth, 2328 W 4th Ave, Vancouver, BC V6K 1P1

featured_reviews.review_id: We enjoyed a delicious Wild Salmon Burger on 'Kits Day 2023' ~ appreciated that there was a Table & Chairs outside the store where you could sit to eat and enjoy.  One of our group vowed that she didn't like Salmon but she sure enjoyed this Salmon Burger and is now a 'convert'.  The $15 cost was well worth it for a freshly grilled generous Salmon portion~ hope we get to enjoy the same next year!  A small favour ~ It would be nice to have the option of different types of Buns, besides a White Bun ~ thank you!

featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text:
Thank you so much for sharing your positive experience with us and for taking the time to leave such a wonderful review. We're thrilled to hear that you enjoyed our Wild Salmon Burger on 'Kits Day 2023' and that it was a hit with your group, even converting a self-proclaimed non-salmon lover!

Your feedback regarding the bun options is greatly appreciated, and we'll definitely take it into consideration for future events.

Thank you again for your kind words and support.

featured_reviews.review_id: Came into the store today after a few months, and was really pleasantly surprised. The display counters have been redone, the displays look far more appealing, and I was really happy to see fresh sockeye from Barclay Sound (it always seems to be previously frozen, which I don't mind as the price is a bit better). I need to go back and pick up some frozen shrimp. Love the selection in the frozen section. Keep up the great work!

Today I purchased ingredients for a Westcoast seafood dinner (pictured, minus the sushi), and all my guests complimented the wonderful seafood.

featured_reviews.review_id:
This year we were late for canning Sockeye salmon.  After phoning several places and not having any success we stumbled on to 7 seas.

Spoke with Stevie who said yes they had Sockeye. The price was quite reasonable.

We got our Salmon. They dressed, cleaned and cut off the fins - ready for canning.

The fish was fresh and the service was superb. They have many other varieties of fresh and frozen fish and sea food.  And sauces and spices. I also talked with Cato, the store manager and knowledgeable about their products. They are oceanwise.

Highly recommend this place.

featured_reviews.review_id: Don't think leaving 40 bones in a 1lb  piece of salmon is acceptable. The explanation is its processed in Richmond plant now so it's ok. Don't think so
featured_reviews.review_text: Don't think leaving 40 bones in a 1lb  piece of salmon is acceptable. The explanation is its processed in Richmond plant now so it's ok. Don't think so
featured_reviews.response_from_owner_text: Hi Donna, this was a miscommuncation. I'm sorry for your poor experience. Please be sure to ask for fish that is pin boned removed at any fish monger as fin fish almost always contains bones (excepting shark and sturgeon which has cartilage instead). Usually bones are all removed but admittedly, sometimes they are not based on manpower or coordination of inventory and supply options.
